							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok.. last night I logged into Beta (no raids this week... We called them off... WOOHOO!)
<br />

<br />
I read up on some of my stuff that was patched etc... on Friday I had logged in and tested Graceful Avoidence and was pretty PO'd about it.
<br />

<br />
Test subject on both Friday and Tues was Firetoad named magma wurm in LS.
<br />

<br />
Friday lvl 43
<br />
Tuesday lvl 42
<br />

<br />
On Friday I had to run when magmawurm was at 90% HP.
<br />
On Tuesday I died and got him to 39%... nothing spectacular... but it was more of an improve over 90%
<br />

<br />
I could have beaten him on Tues... using mez and regen technique.... but that's boring as hell and not a good test.
<br />

<br />
After I failed... I found Suretu... old buddy form EQ1 veeshan server I haven't gotten to see in game for about 3 years or so... he happens to be a 51 Dirge.
<br />

<br />
A quick comparison of gear and spells... I was way ahead.... he is not in a raiding guild.
<br />

<br />
However he did have a 1 lvl advantage and is supposed to be the "bard golden child sub-class" of DoF.
<br />

<br />
I sent him up against Firetoad... and he did about the same... which because of gear differences and level differences is about what I expected.
<br />

<br />
We had 2 attempts each (I did 1 before Suretu got there... then he did 2 and then I did 1 more) and it worked out similar each time.
<br />

<br />
We then grouped... looked at our buffs a little... buffed up... and tag teamed Firetoad.  Dirge + Troub obviously not the best combo....
<br />

<br />
We won... as was expected... I was the "tank" and had about 50-60% HP left and Suretu never took damage.   It would have worked out better if the player with the better gear was the Dirge... my regens are great... but lifetaps don't help much when you are not taking the damage... if Suretu had my gear and had tanked we might have both been full HP.
<br />

<br />
Keep in mind... it was a NAMED and HEROIC... but also 8 levels lower than me... 9 levels lower than Suretu.
<br />

<br />
Now... me and Suretu could probably have done slightly better... but we are both 2 boxers... so our "solo-style" is not perfect.  I am pretty postive I could have 2-boxed it with ease (with my 50 fury)  
<br />

<br />
As 2 boxers we kind of had a chat about aggro... apparently our Swansong/Discordant Boon aggro was lowered... alot.  For some of you this will be a good thing... however it was our main aggro tool if we wanted to tank in a duo.  I will have to seach for a new aggro tool... this will screw me up quite a bit.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thedauntless.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://tinyurl.com/6qjqw/blah.png" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
